The paper presents a new index structure for answering shortest path and distance queries on road networks, which involves algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the practical performance of the proposed method on real road networks, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of heuristics and optimization techniques in the proposed method may also suggest a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
